  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&quot;M&#xE9;xico Inf&#xF3;rmate is a network of journalists working at the state level, testing how Mexico&#x2019;s transparency and access to information reforms can improve investigative journalism outside of Mexico City. This grant to Sonora Ciudadana would allow M&#xE9;xico Inf&#xF3;rmate to consolidate a centralized coordination body, while continuing to work on training local journalists in the use of access to information systems in their states, culminating in a national convening for peer exchange and dissemination of the impact of the state level work.&quot;</narrative>
  </description>
